<div class="section">
    <h2>JMdict / JMdictDB</h2>

    <div class="dataset-box">
        <p>
            Japanese dictionary data used in Toori may be derived from
            <strong>JMdict</strong>, provided by the
            <strong>Electronic Dictionary Research and Development Group (EDRDG)</strong>.
        </p>

        <ul>
            <li><strong>Dataset:</strong> JMdict / JMdictDB</li>
            <li><strong>Provider:</strong> Electronic Dictionary Research and Development Group</li>
            <li><strong>License:</strong> Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International</li>
        </ul>

        <p>
            Original source:
            <a href="https://www.edrdg.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
                https://www.edrdg.org/
            </a>
        </p>

        <p>
            License details:
            <a href="https://www.edrdg.org/edrdg/licence.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
                https://www.edrdg.org/edrdg/licence.html
            </a>
        </p>

        <p>
            Data used in Toori may have been:
        </p>

        <ul>
            <li>parsed from source format</li>
            <li>filtered</li>
            <li>normalized</li>
            <li>restructured</li>
            <li>converted into SQLite database format</li>
        </ul>

        <p>
            Public adapted dataset:
            <a href="datasets/jmdict_dictionary.db">
                Download Toori JMdict-derived dictionary database
            </a>
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

